article.headline: ETSU 88, North Florida 57
article.story: JOHNSON CITY, Tenn. -- Courtney Pigram scored 24 points to lead East Tennessee State to an 88-57 win over North Florida on Monday night. Pigram shot 9-for-14, including five 3-pointers for the Bucs (10-4, 4-0 Atlantic Sun Conference). Micah Williams chipped in with 15 points and five rebounds. The Ospreys (2-12, 0-4 Atlantic Sun) were paced by Kyle Groothuis, who scored 11 points on 5-of-8 shooting. Groothuis also grabbed a game high seven rebounds. The Bucs outrebounded North Florida 45-31, and scored 21 points off the Ospreys' 13 turnovers. ETSU shot 51.5 percent from the floor (34-for-66), hitting 11 3-pointers along the way. The Bucs had 17 assists as a team. North Florida struggled from the free-throw line, making only 1 of 6 attempts.
